SIMPLE: structural_shape
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Structural shape
<hw>Struc"tur*al shape</hw>. <fld>(Engin. & Arch.)</fld> <def>The shape
of a member especially adapted to structural purposes, esp. in giving
the greatest strength with the least material.</def>
<specif>Hence,</specif> <mark>Colloq.</mark>, <def>any steel or iron
member of such shape, as channel irons, <universbold>I</universbold>
beams, <universbold>T</universbold> beams, etc., or, sometimes, a
column, girder, etc., built up with such members.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Structural steel</ent>⟦br⟧
